{
  "stem": "3382.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I told them what I think-- that they could find a better representative for AK.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because on account of-- I told them, on account of such son-of-a-bitches like Pilch that thousands of good, Polish people perished.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because Soviets never forgot what AK, certain units of AK, did to them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Were you at the Zapole estate for the rest of the war?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Or did you leave at some point?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let me finish up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The 42nd year-- 1942 somehow went through.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a terrible thing what the Germans did to Lida Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In May of '42, I think it was the 8th, they surrounded the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A couple of weeks before, they took out all Jews which were in Lida Ghetto from Vilna, all the Vilna Jews, and shot them, something like 60, 70 people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know exactly, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then I remembered that on that day-- day before, I went-- I had to do some contact.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I went to that parson-- to that parson.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Slaski-- the Colonel Slaski from the Nowogrodek district was a son of a bitch, too-- anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he didn't do anything about Lieutenant Pilch, despite the fact that the, the main command from Warsaw wrote him a letter about his-- activities of some of his officers, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But at that time, I separated his group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And with no-- any information, which we used to do, would go to Nowogrodek.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We, we, we were afraid, you know, of being betrayed there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on that day, you know, they surrounded the ghetto and took out a couple thousand Jews, and shot them in Ponary.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not in Ponary, in a place called Kaszary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Three or four days before, Jews dug there a big ditch.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
